        <!-- Slide 3: What is MAIHDA? -->
        <div class="slide">
            <div class="slide-header">
                <h2>What is MAIHDA?</h2>
                <span class="slide-number">3/12</span>
            </div>
            <div class="slide-content">
                <h3>Multilevel Analysis of Individual Heterogeneity and Discriminatory Accuracy</h3>
                
                <div class="key-point">
                    <p><strong>The "Gold Standard" for Quantitative Intersectional Analysis</strong></p>
                    <p>Treats intersectional identities as random effects in multilevel models, revealing how multiple characteristics combine to create unique experiences beyond simple additive effects</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="two-column">
                    <div>
                        <h3>Conventional Approach:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Examines factors separately</li>
                            <li>Assumes additive effects</li>
                            <li>Misses critical intersections</li>
                            <li>Generic policy recommendations</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>MAIHDA Approach:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Creates intersectional strata</li>
                            <li>Reveals multiplicative effects</li>
                            <li>Handles small cell sizes via shrinkage</li>
                            <li>Enables targeted interventions</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="yellow-box">
                    <p><strong>Three Extended MAIHDA Applications:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Spatial MAIHDA</strong> → School Segregation Study</li>
                        <li><strong>Longitudinal MAIHDA</strong> → Teacher Retention Study</li>
                        <li><strong>Policy Evaluation MAIHDA</strong> → Transport & Accessibility Study</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 4: Study 1 - Current Approach -->
        <div class="slide">
            <div class="slide-header">
                <h2>Study 1: Ethnic School Segregation - Current Approach</h2>
                <span class="slide-number">4/12</span>
            </div>
            <div class="slide-content">
                <div class="two-column">
                    <div>
                        <h3>Research Question</h3>
                        <p>How do ethnic clustering patterns vary across schools, local authorities, and over time in England?</p>
                        
                        <h3>Current Method</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Three-level multilevel model</li>
                            <li>Years → Local Authorities → Regions</li>
                            <li>Observation unit: Segregation scores (LA-year level)</li>
                            <li>Entropy-based segregation index</li>
                            <li>Examines factors separately</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <div class="formula">
                            Y_tij = γ₀₀₀ + β₁(Selective)_ij + β₂(Academies)_ij + β₃(Faith)_ij + β₄(% ethnic)_ij + u₀₀j + r₀ij + e_tij
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div>
                        <h3>Key Finding</h3>
                        <p class="emphasis">Counterintuitive: Higher ethnic % = Lower concentration</p>
                        
                        <div class="variance-chart">
                            <div class="bar-group">
                                <div class="stacked-bar" style="height: 250px;">
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 30%; background: #FFB6C1;"></div>
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 41%; background: #87CEEB;"></div>
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 26%; background: #98FB98;"></div>
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 3%; background: #D3D3D3;"></div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="bar-label">Bangladeshi</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bar-group">
                                <div class="stacked-bar" style="height: 250px;">
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 44%; background: #FFB6C1;"></div>
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 21%; background: #87CEEB;"></div>
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 26%; background: #98FB98;"></div>
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 9%; background: #D3D3D3;"></div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="bar-label">Indian</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bar-group">
                                <div class="stacked-bar" style="height: 250px;">
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 61%; background: #FFB6C1;"></div>
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 31%; background: #87CEEB;"></div>
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 5%; background: #98FB98;"></div>
                                    <div class="bar-segment" style="height: 3%; background: #D3D3D3;"></div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="bar-label">White British</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="legend">
                            <div class="legend-item">
                                <div class="legend-color" style="background: #FFB6C1;"></div>
                                <span>Year</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="legend-item">
                                <div class="legend-color" style="background: #87CEEB;"></div>
                                <span>Local Authority</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="legend-item">
                                <div class="legend-color" style="background: #98FB98;"></div>
                                <span>Region</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="key-point">
                    <p><strong>Limitation:</strong> Cannot explain WHY this happens differently for different groups or WHERE spatial clusters of disadvantage exist</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 5: Study 1 - Spatial MAIHDA Enhancement -->
        <div class="slide">
            <div class="slide-header">
                <h2>Study 1: Spatial MAIHDA Enhancement</h2>
                <span class="slide-number">5/12</span>
            </div>
            <div class="slide-content">
                <h3>Spatial MAIHDA Innovation</h3>
                <div class="two-column">
                    <div>
                        <h4>Method Enhancement:</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>48 intersectional strata: Ethnicity × SES × School Type</li>
                            <li>Cross-classified with spatial units (LSOAs)</li>
                            <li>Spatial weights matrix for autocorrelation</li>
                            <li>Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation (10,000 simulations)</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <div class="formula">
                            Y_ijk = γ₀ + (1|strata_j) + (1|spatial_k) + W*spatial_effects + ε_ijk
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div>
                        <h4>Simulated Results:</h4>
                        <table class="results-table">
                            <tr>
                                <th>Intersectional Group</th>
                                <th>Segregation Index</th>
                                <th>Spatial Clustering</th>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Pakistani × Low SES × Faith School</td>
                                <td class="highlight-cell">142.5</td>
                                <td>Moran's I = 0.82</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>White British × High SES × Academy</td>
                                <td>45.2</td>
                                <td>Moran's I = 0.21</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Black × Low SES × Community</td>
                                <td>118.3</td>
                                <td>Moran's I = 0.67</td>
                            </tr>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h3>Monte Carlo Spatial Simulation</h3>
                <div class="chart-container" style="height: 300px;">
                    <svg viewBox="0 0 800 300" style="width: 100%; height: 100%;">
                        <!-- Background grid -->
                        <defs>
                            <pattern id="grid" width="40" height="40" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
                                <path d="M 40 0 L 0 0 0 40" fill="none" stroke="#e0e0e0" stroke-width="1"/>
                            </pattern>
                        </defs>
                        <rect width="800" height="300" fill="url(#grid)" />
                        
                        <!-- Spatial clusters visualization -->
                        <circle cx="150" cy="100" r="60" fill="#FF6B6B" opacity="0.6"/>
                        <circle cx="200" cy="130" r="45" fill="#FF6B6B" opacity="0.6"/>
                        <circle cx="180" cy="180" r="35" fill="#FF6B6B" opacity="0.6"/>
                        <text x="175" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="bold">High Segregation</text>
                        <text x="175" y="155" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10">Pakistani×LowSES</text>
                        
                        <circle cx="450" cy="150" r="30" fill="#4ECDC4" opacity="0.6"/>
                        <circle cx="500" cy="140" r="25" fill="#4ECDC4" opacity="0.6"/>
                        <text x="475" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12">Low Segregation</text>
                        
                        <circle cx="650" cy="120" r="50" fill="#FFE66D" opacity="0.6"/>
                        <circle cx="680" cy="160" r="40" fill="#FFE66D" opacity="0.6"/>
                        <text x="665" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12">Moderate</text>
                        
                        <!-- Arrow showing spatial spillover -->
                        <path d="M 250 140 Q 350 100 430 140" fill="none" stroke="#333" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>
                        <defs>
                            <marker id="arrowhead" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="7" refX="10" refY="3.5" orient="auto">
                                <polygon points="0 0, 10 3.5, 0 7" fill="#333"/>
                            </marker>
                        </defs>
                        <text x="340" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10">Spatial Spillover</text>
                    </svg>
                </div>
                
                <div class="key-point">
                    <p><strong>Key Finding:</strong> Monte Carlo reveals 95% CI [135.2, 149.8] for Pakistani×LowSES×Faith clusters. Spatial autocorrelation shows segregation "hot spots" requiring targeted intervention in specific neighborhoods, not just schools.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 6: Study 2 - Current Survival Analysis -->
        <div class="slide">
            <div class="slide-header">
                <h2>Study 2: Teacher Retention - Current Approach</h2>
                <span class="slide-number">6/12</span>
            </div>
            <div class="slide-content">
                <h3>Survival Analysis Results</h3>
                
                <div class="two-column">
                    <div>
                        <h4>Current Method:</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Cox proportional hazards model</li>
                            <li>650,000 teachers tracked</li>
                            <li>Shows WHO leaves and WHEN</li>
                            <li>Cannot explain intersectional vulnerabilities</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4>Key Statistics:</h4>
                        <table style="margin-top: 20px;">
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>Group</strong></td>
                                <td><strong>11-Year Retention</strong></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Female</td>
                                <td>16.54%</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Male</td>
                                <td>12.96%</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>With ITT</td>
                                <td>16.85%</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>No ITT</td>
                                <td>9.75%</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>White British</td>
                                <td>15.88%</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Ethnic Minority</td>
                                <td>13.50%</td>
                            </tr>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div>
                        <h4>Kaplan-Meier Survival Curves:</h4>
                        <div class="retention-plot">
                            <div class="survival-curve">
                                <svg viewBox="0 0 450 350">
                                    <!-- Axes -->
                                    <line x1="50" y1="300" x2="400" y2="300" stroke="#333" stroke-width="2"/>
